title: For Sale:  Brand New LaRue PredatOBR 5.56 FDE 14.5" with Surefire brake
postcontent:
Up for sale is a brand new, never broken down, cleaned, loaded or fired LaRue PredatOBR 'take down' rifle in 5.56.  It has the 14.5" barrel with attached Surefire brake.  Comes in the factory FDE hard case with all original tools. Over a year wait for these!

Not interested in any trades or low ball offers.  This is the real deal and can be yours TODAY!

Info from LaRue:

NEW LaRue Tactical PredatOBR 14.5” 5.56. The PredatOBR 5.56 was designed for those who are searching for a hybrid cross between the standard OBR and PredatAR 5.56x45 Rifles. The PredatOBR takes the highly accurate OBR 5.56 design, and lightens it in every possible way with the least-possible impact to the accuracy that the standard OBR is known for.  PredatOBR barrels are chambered in 5.56x45mm, and feature rifling in a 1/8 twist rate. All muzzles are threaded in 1/2 x 28. Like the OBR and PredatAR riles, LaRue has eliminated the conventional AR barrel nut and bolt the handguard directly to the proprietary upper receiver, creating a true “free-float” barrel. The handguard does not touch the barrel or barrel nut at any place. The zero-MOA upper rail provides plenty of room for weapon-mounted night-vision day/night combinations. Both the upper and lower are CNC-machined from billet aluminum for the optimum fit and consistency. Even though it has been lightened certain features, there is still additional material in strategic areas to achieve maximum accuracy.  The PredatOBR has threaded stainless-steel hard-points over the entire length of the handguard at the 3, 6, and 9 o’clock positions. These hard-points have an integral spine built-in for structural support. Provided with the system are three 3-inch MIL-STD-1913 rail sections that can be positioned anywhere along the handguard, per operator preference. These rail sections are attachable/detachable using a supplied tool (Torx® T-15 wrench). The rail sections are CNC-machined from billet aluminum. This robust solution provides a perfect precision mounting space for aiming lasers, illumination and bipods. The PredatOBR's Port Selector Technology™ (PST) gas block is adjustable, to aid in the optimum function when using a sound suppressor. This special gas block contains a dual port mechanism that is operated by rotating a lever from one side to another. When the lever is rotated to the right-side of the rifle, the gasses are reduced, to compensate for the extra blowback created by the suppressor. When rotated to the left side, the gasses are increased for use without a suppressor. The LaRue Tactical 6-position Retract Action Trigger (R.A.T.) Stock comes standard with every PredatOBR. It is ergonomic, has protected control surfaces and contains a set of cleaning rods in an internal compartment. Since the height of the 12 o’clock rail is at the optimum position, there is no need for a cheek riser as part of this system. The New A-PEG grip also comes standard. This grip was designed to be ambidextrous and places the hand in the corrected position for precision shooting.
3ea 3” Rail Sections, Operators Manual, Barrel Wrench, FDE Hard Case also included in this auction!

title: For Sale:  M39 WWII Finnish Infantry Rifle VKT 1942 Mosin Nagant
postcontent:
This is a really nice M39 WWII Finnish infantry rifle.
1942 VKT (Valmet) made rifle on a Westinghouse (WWI USA Made) M91 receiver.
Caliber - 7.62x54R Rimmed Russian - so you can feed it Cheap Russian surplus ammo.

These M39's are about the best of the Mosin Nagant family of rifles out there.
They feature super accurate Finnish made barrels and were carefully hand fitted by the Finns for maximum accuracy.  The military standard was under 1" at 100 yards.

Westinghouse made M91 infantry rifles for the Russian Government during WWI.
The Finns bought and captured many Russian rifles during their independence wars as well as during WWII.  These were later converted/recycled for their own use.

Post war square splice stock
Numbers match
Stock shows the usual armory storage wear.
Rifling appears to be excellent/near excellent condition. 
You don't see many of these old war horses with such beautiful bores.

Please note - there was no choice for "Valmet", "VKT", or "Finnish Army" in the Manufacturer's list - so I picked SAKO - another Finn manufacturer of these rifles.
It is NOT a Sako, but rather a VKT.

Face to Face only - no shipping.  
Please email me if you have any questions.
Thanks

title: For Sale:  M91 1915 WWI Infantry Rifle Westinghouse Mosin Nagant
postcontent:
Here's a nice Westinghouse M91 infantry rifle
Made in 1915 by Westinghouse (Here in the Good 'Ole USA) for the Imperial Russian Government for WWI.

This is the "Original" Mosin Nagant Long rifle for Russian infantry use.
It shoots 7.62x54R Rimmed Russian - so it will take Cheap Russian surplus ammo.

At some point - it ended up in the hands of the Finnish army - you can see that from the Finnish Civil Guard markings (The big S and cancelled numbers on the receiver) 
The stock is a Finnish Army stock - apparently replaced when the original stock was broken or damaged during war.  This is fairly typical of these rifles.  It has a nice, visible Finn cartouche on the stock.  Surprisingly, the vast majority of the rifle is still Westinghouse.  This is not typical - as the Finns assembled random parts as needed to get a working rifle (Much like the US Military has done since WWI)

This rifle went to the Russians - so it does not have any "US Ordinance" stampings on it.  It does have the Russian acceptance stamps on the metal, as well as the Finnish Army stampings on the metal and stock.

Externally - it shows wear.  This rifle has seen war.
The stock has a chip in the forend.
The barrel is also well used - the lands are slightly rounded and the grooves are a little dark.  You can see that the rifling is still very strong, though.

Please note - there is no Manufacturer Category for "Westinghouse" or "Russian Military" - so I listed it as "Sako" - another Finnish company.  It is NOT made by Sako.

Face to face sale only.
Please email me if you have any questions.

The Marlin Model 99M1 is a short carbine with the same tubular magazine and action as the Marlin 99 and 99U. The main difference is the 99M1 has a walnut stock and hand guard and an 18-inch barrel to make it look more like a US military M1 Carbine. Marlin introduced the 99M1 in 1964, in hopes that the resemblance to the US M1 carbine would appeal to the thousands of WW II veterans who had trained with and carried into combat the larger caliber US M1.
